title: Side Chair, 1785–90
description: Rectangular open back with a top rail crested with debased leaf and dart moulding.  Back consists of three  vertical pierced splat elements in narrow V-forms with honey-suckle blossoms.  Shaped upholstered seat.  Square tapered straight front legs; inlaid lines on front surface.  Upholstery is rose-colored.

tombstone.epitaph:
Side Chair, 1785–90.
1785–90. mahogany, carved and inlaid. Gift of Sarah Cooper Hewitt. 1931-84-17.
